DataElement.preferredName: Electrospray Ionization Instrumentation Interface Device Component Manufacturer java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A procedure used in mass spectrometry analysis. Means of delivering nonvolatile analytes into the gas phase for mass analysis. Best used on molecules which are charged in solution or readily accept a charge. Particularly well suited to the analysis of biomolecules. Can be used to probe tertiary structure and non-covalent interactions (from NCSU Mass Spectrometry Facility web site):Any object, or item of electrical or electronic equipment, which is designed to carry out a specific function or set of functions._Either a program that controls a display for the user and that allows the user to interact with the system or a computer circuit consisting of the hardware and associated circuitry that links one device with another.:A person, an enterprise, or an entity that produces finished goods._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
